he door OUTWARD/away from the machine — direction not specified by the prompt for the door specifically, this is a judgment call, flagging it); `flap_open` is nested inside that so it works independently or combined; `tray_out_pct` wired into `spring_tray()`'s own Y-translate only (not `tray_rack()`'s, which stays fixed to the machine) via a new local `tray_y = tray_start_d - tray_d*tray_out_pct`. TASK 3: `rules-dimensions.md` v12→v13 — old "Door Z range 50-300mm" row marked SUPERSEDED (kept, not deleted, matching the bell-collar convention) + new "VM-01 Base — Left-Zone Front Door" section added with all 10 confirmed entries verbatim per prompt, including the hinge-hardware-spec OPEN ITEM. JUDGMENT CALLS flagged (not silently made): (a) window's right-side margin mirrors `window_margin_side` from `door_right_x` (prompt said "matching margin," no separate right-margin parameter given); (b) acrylic pane / new flap reuse existing `door_t`/`flap_t` globals for thickness (no new thickness parameter was specified); (c) `hinge_od` reused for the stopper-rod diameter (no rod-diameter parameter given); (d) `flap_w`/`flap_h`/`hinge_h` globals deleted as fully dead code (superseded 1:1 by `exit_w`/`exit_h`, `hinge_h` had zero remaining callers) rather than kept-but-unused, to avoid this project's recurring "dormant global" bug class — `flap_t`/`hinge_od` kept since reused. NOT touched, confirmed out of scope per DO NOT TOUCH: `outer_shell_debug()` (v40's fix untouched), `acrylic_display()` (untouched). ⚑ FLAG (discovered, not fixed): `tray_zone_frame()`'s comment still says "matches spring_zone_panel() Z 300-700" — that module no longer exists; `tray_zone_frame()` itself (code) was not in TASK 1's removal list so left entirely unmodified, comment now stale — flagging for a follow-up doc-only cleanup. The pre-existing v38-era stale STL filenames in the RENDER MODE comment block (top of file, references `VM-01-v38-*.stl`) also confirmed still present, unrelated to this prompt's